<td align="left" width="198">&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>
</div>
</center>
    <p><font face="Arial" size="2"><li>The discussions in the meeting followed 
  the <a href="#agenda">agenda</a> below , which included work 
  on the following issues:<br>
&nbsp;<p>
  <ul type="disc">
<li>Following the Mandate of the Declaration of Buenos Aires, the 
    delegations focused on eliminating the brackets from articles 3.5 to 3.7, 
    7.2 and 5 of the Draft Chapter on Competition Policy, relating to 
    Institutional Provisions, Competition Policy Review Mechanism, Consultations 
    and Dispute Settlement, and Confidentiality<br>
    <br>
<li>In response to the questions of the Smaller Economies and Countries 
    without Competition Policy, the delegations of Costa Rica and the United 
    States each made a presentation on Questions 1 and 2 of the document 
    &quot;Proposal by Smaller Economies and Countries without Competition Law&#8221;<br>
    <br>
<li>Similarly, the Andean Community made a presentation on its experience with 
    its common competition regime, by way of response to Question 3 of the 
    document &#8220;Proposal by Smaller Economies and Countries without Competition 
    Law&#8221;<br>
&nbsp;</p>
<li>In addition, the NGCP worked on a format for presentation the Report to 
  the TNC, on the Proposal of the Smaller Economies and Countries without 
  Competition Law</p>
</ul>  
</ol>
&nbsp;<p>
<hr width="70%">
<p align="center">
<b><u>FTAA - NEGOTIATING GROUP ON COMPETITION POLICY</u><p align="center">Fourteenth Meeting<br>
  <br>
Panama City, Panama, November 6 - 9, 2001
<p align="center">
<a name="agenda" href="#top">AGENDA</a></b> <br>
<p align="left">
<ol>
<li>Elimination of Brackets from Articles 3.5 to 3.7, 7.2 and 5 of the Draft 
Chapter on Competition Policy <br>
<br>
<li>Drafting of the Report to the Trade Negotiations Committee on the conclusions 
of the NGCP on the Study on Antidumping and Regional Trade Agreements<br>
<br>
<li>Presentation by the delegations of Costa Rica and the United States on 
Questions 1 and 2 of the document, using as a guide the Proposed Framework for 
Questions 3, 4 and 5 in the Proposal by Smaller Economies and Countries without 
Competition Law
<br>
<br>
<li>Presentation by the Andean Community on its experience with its common 
competition regime, by way of response to Question 3 of the document, on the 
Proposal by Smaller Economies and Countries without Competition Law
<br>
<br>
<li>Establishment of a system for grouping and submitting to the TNC 
presentations made by delegations in response to the Mandate in the Proposal by 
Smaller Economies and Countries without Competition Law
<br>
<br>
<li>Other business
<br>
</ol>
    </li></font>
</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    </center>    
   
